-- Thunder Rally to Defeat Heat 105-94 in First Game of NBA Finals
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2012-06-13T03:42:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/thunder-rally-to-defeat-heat-105-94-in-first-game-of-nba-finals.html
Kevin Durant  scored 36 points and
Russell Westbrook had 27 as the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied
from a 13-point deficit during the first half to defeat the
Miami Heat 105-94 in the opening game of the National Basketball
Association Finals.  The teams return to the Chesapeake Energy Arena in Oklahoma
City on June 14 for the second game in the best-of-seven series.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  